  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, we provided participants with the unconditional right to access, revise, remove, and limit the use of their personal data.",
    "Participants filled in the German version of the Social Phobia Inventory (SPIN 42) prior to their participation in the clinical interview.",
    "SPIN is a 17-item inventory that evaluates social anxiety symptom severity 44.",
    "It refers to the past seven days, assessing fear, avoidance, and physiological symptoms.",
    "Answers are scored on a five point Likert-scale ranging from 0 to 4, where 0 indicates no symptoms and 4 indicates severe symptoms, leading to scores ranging from 0 to 68."
  ],
